From Charles M Kozierok Subject Re WHAT'S WITH ALL THESE SCORES In article Joseph Hernandez writes In article senator Charles M Kozierok writes In article Sean Garrison writes Stuff about upated inning scores at just that exact time to see the even results after the game is over are not necessary thanks to Hernandez who posts daily standings and results here every Am I supposed to take that as a compliment or a put down Just it was meant entirely as a I do this as a service to the entire baseball world on USENET especially for those in the East Coast who can't get final scores for West Coast games in their newspapers or late TV This is helpful to fans in other countries who either receive only weekly scores or updates by the Also many have requested for this kind of service previously but it was only available through BBS's or some pay news By the way mine is free of charge and has no copyright i was not trying to criticize your service at in fact i was trying to encourage others to use i don't personally use it but i'm sure others do and that was my point in posting there is no need for individuals to duplicate in an ad hoc fashion what you have already if you want to send updates and scores set up a private mailing list and use Remember I only post final scores and the updated standings once a day to the Other than that everything is done through private e Currently there are people on my mailing list that branches off into other mailing lists available for many And the list grows by an average of people a having one person such as yourself who does it is a great having do it is that's keep up the good work charles